<item>
            <title>[SOLR-9255] Rename SOLR_AUTHENTICATION_CLIENT_CONFIGURER -&gt; SOLR_AUTHENTICATION_CLIENT_BUILDER</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-9255</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I configured SSL and BasicAuthentication with Rule-Based-Authorization.&lt;br/&gt;
I noticed that since the latest changes from 6.0.1 to 6.1.0 I cannot pass the Basic Authentication Credentials to the Solr Start Script anymore. For the previous release I did this via the bin/solr.in.sh shellscript.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What has happened with the SOLR_AUTHENTICATION_CLIENT_CONFIGURER and SOLR_AUTHENTICATION_OPTS parameters? Are they still in use or is there a new way to pass basic auth credentials on the command-line?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
